Here’s a straight-English version:

---

To all the self-styled independent tough guys in Australia: the government is still being ridiculous and dishonest. But is anyone really surprised? When you have a prime minister with no charisma, no presence and no clue in charge, of course the result is a dysfunctional government.

It feels like every day they’re basically saying to the public, “Friend, can I borrow some money? Please?” The whole thing is pure theatre. I’m honestly surprised they haven’t created a Minister for Whatever’s Trending Online or a Parliamentary Secretary for Luxury Instagram Chocolate.

One issue I’ve been posting about a lot is AI safety. Australia could be genuinely world-class at deploying this technology safely, but right now there’s more low-quality AI nonsense than in a bloated consulting report. Honestly, it annoys me a lot.

Whenever the government talks about AI, all they do is brag about the huge productivity boost it’s supposed to bring. Grok, is that even true? It’s like watching Speed try a backflip: the enthusiasm is there, but all they’re leaning into is the dangerous part.

Our government needs to get serious and be willing to use strong, hard-edged regulation.

To all the industry insiders who argue that AI companies should be allowed to train on copyrighted material for free, I have only one response: absolutely not, sit down.

Some of the younger crowd think I’m just chasing clicks, but I’m going to keep posting provocative criticism until their arguments fall apart.

So, to all you “sigmas”: keep posting with some hope. Keep working on yourselves and keep giving it your best. The people who understand, understand.

Oh, and: sixty-seven.
